author: kpvdr
msg: [For Andrew Stitcher] inlined qpid::sys::check() in APRBase.h; This is called a lot - for every call to an APR call, inlining this seems to give about 8% speed in my tests (even though originally check() only seemed to use 1-2% of the time). I think this must be a 2nd order instruction caching effect.
